        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(agents): add description field for dynamic agent discovery",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nSurfaces configured agent descriptions through `agents_list` so orchestrator agents can understand sub-agent capabilities at runtime.\n\nThis was originally requested in #7490. Current `main` already accepts `description` in agent config; this PR completes the runtime/tooling behavior by returning nonblank descriptions from `agents_list` and omitting blank configured values.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Update `agents_list` tool output to include trimmed descriptions when set\n- Omit blank configured descriptions from returned agent entries\n- Update `agents_list` tool description and docs to reflect the field\n- Add focused tests for configured nonblank descriptions and blank omission\n- Refresh prompt snapshots / generated config docs baseline as needed\n\n## Use Case\n\nIn multi-agent setups, orchestrators need to route tasks to the right sub-agent without hardcoding catalogs. With this change:\n\n```yaml\nagents:\n  list:\n    - id: analyzer\n      name: Data Analyzer\n      description: 'Statistical analysis, chart generation, anomaly detection'\n    - id: writer\n      name: Report Writer\n      description: 'Summarization, formatting, document generation'\n```\n\n`agents_list` returns:\n```json\n{\n  \"agents\": [\n    { \"id\": \"analyzer\", \"name\": \"Data Analyzer\", \"description\": \"Statistical analysis, chart generation, anomaly detection\", \"configured\": true },\n    { \"id\": \"writer\", \"name\": \"Report Writer\", \"description\": \"Summarization, formatting, document generation\", \"configured\": true }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nThis is fully backward compatible — existing configs without `description` are unaffected.\n\nCloses #7490\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: `agents_list` now returns configured nonblank `agents.list[].description` values and omits blank configured descriptions.\n- Real environment tested: local OpenClaw Gateway built from this PR branch at head `ea4113c4c2`, isolated `OPENCLAW_HOME=/tmp/openclaw-pr75225-proof`, loopback Gateway `127.0.0.1:19977`, plugins disabled, no production Shannon runtime touched.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```sh\nOPENCLAW_HOME=/tmp/openclaw-pr75225-proof \\\nOPENCLAW_STATE_DIR=/tmp/openclaw-pr75225-proof/.openclaw \\\nOPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH=/tmp/openclaw-pr75225-proof/.openclaw/openclaw.json \\\nnode openclaw.mjs --log-level info gateway --port 19977 --bind loopback\n\ncurl -sS http://127.0.0.1:19977/tools/invoke \\\n  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\n  -H 'x-openclaw-scopes: operator.write' \\\n  -d '{\"tool\":\"agents_list\",\"action\":\"json\",\"args\":{},\"sessionKey\":\"agent:main:proof\"}'\n```\n\n  Proof config: requester `main` has `subagents.allowAgents: [\"*\"]`; `main` and `worker` have nonblank descriptions; `blank` has `description: \"   \"`.\n\n- Evidence after fix: copied live output from the real Gateway `/tools/invoke` response:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"result\": {\n    \"details\": {\n      \"requester\": \"main\",\n      \"allowAny\": true,\n      \"agents\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"main\",\n          \"name\": \"Main Proof\",\n          \"configured\": true,\n          \"agentRuntime\": { \"id\": \"codex\", \"source\": \"implicit\" },\n          \"description\": \"Primary proof agent description should appear in agents_list.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"blank\",\n          \"name\": \"Blank Proof\",\n          \"configured\": true,\n          \"agentRuntime\": { \"id\": \"codex\", \"source\": \"implicit\" }\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"worker\",\n          \"name\": \"Worker Proof\",\n          \"configured\": true,\n          \"agentRuntime\": { \"id\": \"codex\", \"source\": \"implicit\" },\n          \"description\": \"Handles focused backend proof tasks.\"\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n- Observed result after fix: nonblank descriptions are present for `main` and `worker`; the blank configured description for `blank` is omitted from the returned entry.\n- What was not tested: multi-host or production Shannon runtime behavior was not tested; the proof intentionally used an isolated loopback Gateway so no production OpenClaw runtime or secrets were touched.\n- Proof limitations or environment constraints: this is a local Gateway proof, not a full fleet proof. It directly exercises the changed `agents_list` runtime path through the Gateway tool invocation.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\nAdditional validation on the same rebased head:\n\n```sh\npnpm build\n./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check src/agents/tools/agents-list-tool.ts src/agents/openclaw-tools.agents.test.ts src/agents/tools/agents-list-tool.test.ts docs/tools/subagents.md docs/gateway/config-agents.md\n./node_modules/.bin/vitest run src/agents/openclaw-tools.agents.test.ts src/agents/tools/agents-list-tool.test.ts\npnpm prompt:snapshots:check\npnpm config:docs:check\n```\n\nResults: build passed; format passed; focused Vitest passed (4 files / 28 tests); prompt snapshots current (7 files); config docs baseline OK.\n",
